column5: Talked to my son last night and we are just waiting to hear that Tim Hale has huts out, any reports on ice conditions yet?

There are reports on the Lake Simcoe board but they're all bad.....poor ice now, warm temps & windy forecast makes for a bit longer of a wait I'm afraid.  The latest one says there is some ice from Beaverton out to Thorah Island but it's sketchy with open water beyond that.
No ice here, but a handfull of boats were out.
And the tune was barking, take me out, take me out
And the tune was barking, take me out, take me out  Might of been, but not today. Worked so much the past two weeks, I did a sleep in.

I just checked the cooks bay report...about ten or fifteen feet out from shore (west side) there is a bit of ice then the bay is all open water...cold temps starting Wednesday...I'd guess a couple more weeks...
Ice on sturgeon and the.bog cliff just went out for a tour of lake few huts out and some perch being caught
Thanks guys, guess we'll have to wait a few more weeks for Simco. Anyone going for crappie on Scugog that wouldn't mind and old fart tagging along?
